      {
        "turn": 1,
        "name": "Act 1",
        "intent": "[The inquiry room wakes under a low, uneasy light: benches filling, wet coats steaming, the sea still audible beyond the walls. A blank space waits on the table where the first exhibit will be laid.]"
      },
      {
        "turn": 5,
        "name": "Act 2",
        "intent": "[The first heat of accusation gutters, leaving the room colder and more exacting. Wet light gathers on the table as if the inquiry has passed from blame into measurement, and every face turns toward what the next paper may undo.]"
      },
      {
        "turn": 10,
        "name": "Act 3",
        "intent": "[The chart is left open under a weight, its wet edge flattening by slow degrees. The inquiry turns from lines and offices toward colder matter: surfaces, locks, and whatever a storm cannot quite wash clean.]"
      },
      {
        "turn": 16,
        "name": "Act 4",
        "intent": "[The lamp-room papers are closed and tied with tape, leaving the table bare except for the chart's pale rectangle in the damp. The room's attention shifts from ownership to presence, from what a lock permits to what the night may have carried through wind and water.]"
      }
    ],
